## Try the Memory API in TypeScript

```bash
npm install @anthropic-ai/sdk
export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
```

```typescript
import Anthropic from "@anthropic-ai/sdk";

const client = new Anthropic();

const response = await client.messages.create({
  model: "claude-sonnet-4-6",
  max_tokens: 1024,
  system: "You are a helpful assistant. Remember what the user tells you.",
  messages: [
    { role: "user", content: "My name is Aquib. I'm building an iOS app called AINews Weekly." }
  ],
  // Required beta header for v1 of the API
  extra_headers: { "anthropic-beta": "memory-2026-04-22" },
  // Memory bucket key — use a stable per-user identifier
  metadata: { user_id: "aquib-123" }
});

console.log(response.content);
```

In a follow-up call with the same `user_id`, ask 'what's my name?' — Claude pulls the memory automatically.
